text:
• coping skill of the day: color breathing • what is color breathing? color breathing is a coping skill that combines imagery with intentional breathing to help modulate intense feelings, stabilize panic, soothe pain, or to even feel more grounded. it's an invaluable tool  for everyone - but is especially beneficial to those who struggle with anxiety, flashbacks, dissociation and more.
.
there are many ways to perform color breathing; customization is key. one of the most common ways is to imagine a very calming color (perhaps blues or purples, or yellows and golds for some) being inhaled deep into your lungs and immediately finding all of the unrest, anxiety or pain inside of you, enveloping it, healing it. then, assign a color to all the upsetting or painful emotions (perhaps reds or oranges or blacks) and watch as that color leaves you with a long exhale. repeat this deep inhaling and exhaling of colors until you feel more at ease. you may even find that the colors change a bit as you start to improve. this version is most commonly used for anxiety, anger, or physical pain. but, some find it helpful for emotions like sadness and grief, embarrassment or shame. ..preferring to inhale invigorating and light colors and exhale the heavy weighted colors of sadness, loneliness or guilt.
.
another method is to concentrate more on the exhale, watching as the colors go from bright fiery shades to cooler tones, like a gradient. or vice versa if you need lightness, warmth or energy. this is particularly useful if you haven't been able to identify *which* feelings you're experiencing or have no idea "what you need" to inhale - you just know it's intense. so, exhaling reds and oranges until you get down to the calmer end of the 'rainbow' can be really effective in dialing things down (or up, if reversed!)
.
there are many ways to customize this tool to work best for you. the more you can truly visualize it and believe in its effectiveness, the more success you'll have! there are also so many other ways to apply this template. how would you go about color breathing? ideas and suggestions from other survivors can often be what makes things click for someone else!
.
💙💚💜

text:
a lot of people suffer with mental health issues. i am one of them. this candle i have lit for you, for the survivors those still fighting through depression, anxiety, ptsd and many more illnesses. know that you’re strong and worthy always. this candle is for you, let it light up your day so you remember you’re loved and wanted. people are here for you and there when you need them. keep fighting you beautiful amazing people. 🌹
i myself have been suffering for nearly 5 years now with depression anxiety and ptsd, my past still is haunting me and causes issues, but i try to put on a smile for my friends, for my family because i don’t want them to worry about me. those who suffer with mental health we say we are fine but we are not, we are hurting inside, we are calling out for help and no one sees the signs of us crying for help. 
not many people know my past or my story, they all see me as happy,  but one day i’m gonna reveal why i’m like this. why i am feeling the way i do. 
we need to spread awareness to people and make sure they know they are loved. a simple message saying hello how are you or i love you is all it takes for some people. to those who are fighting please stay strong, push through and get help ♥️

escuchala.
pero escuchala bien.
mirala.
pero mirala bien.
es una mujer contando que a sus 16 años fue violada por un hombre de 45 años.
es una víctima que representa a miles y miles de mujeres y niñas que sufren lo mismo.

si no te conmueve el llanto de una víctima de la violación, su voz hecha mierda, sus ojos destruidos, su respiración entrecortada, su pecho que se mueve de manera irregular, el problema no es de ellas.
el problema es tuyo.

text:
. #noesno 
sé que hay mil formas para decir sí; 
sé que hay silencios que hablan más que mil palabras 
que serán miradas que revelan lo que quiero, 
es vivir mi libertad. 
para frenar, para evitar sin explicarlo. 
no hay que ser sabio para comprender que… 
no es no, 
y hay una sola forma de decirlo, 
entiéndelo, no es no, 
y no hace falta que lo justifique 
cuando digo no es no, 
no tengo que gritarlo ni sentir vergüenza al decirlo, no. 
no es no, 
no importa si lo digo sonriendo o llorando, 
no es no, 
en cualquier idioma se comprende y queda claro, 
porque no es no, 
con una vez alcanza, no hace falta repetirlo, no es no. 
sé que hay distintos modos de sentir, 
sé que hay secretos que prefiero abrir al viento. 
eso es vivir sin miedo y poder elegir lo que quiero, 
es vivir mi libertad. 
para pensar, para callar sin explicarlo, 
no hay que ser sabio para comprender que… 
no es no, 
y hay una sola forma de decirlo, 
entiéndelo, no es no, 
y no hace falta que lo justifique 
cuando digo no es no, 
no tengo que gritarlo ni sentir vergüenza al decirlo, no. 
no es no, 
no importa si lo digo sonriendo o llorando, 
no es no, 
en cualquier idioma se comprende y queda claro, 
porque no es no, 
con una vez alcanza, no hace falta repetirlo, no es no. 
sé que hay mil formas para decir sí.
.
.
.
#noesno #metoo #yotecreo #miracomonosponemos #girlpower

text:
no 70º aniversário da carta dos direitos humanos, ong divulga o seu mais novo relatório sobre desigualdades. a retrospectiva de 2018 foca em especial na contínua opressão a mulheres em muitos países.no mundo, 49,5% de todas as pessoas são do sexo feminino. mas apenas 17% dos chefes de estado e de governo e 23% dos parlamentares são mulheres. estes dados do novo relatório da anistia internacional, apresentados nesta segunda-feira (10/12), ilustram o longo caminho a ser percorrido para uma verdadeira igualdade de gênero.
"os direitos das mulheres sempre foram classificados abaixo de outros direitos e liberdades", diz o secretário-geral da anistia internacional, kumi naidoo. ele condena os governos "que se mantêm calados e que na realidade pouco fazem para proteger os direitos de metade da população".
em particular, a organização de direitos humanos registrou uma crescente abundância de "sujeitos durões" entre os líderes de estado que defendem políticas xenófobas ou contrárias às mulheres. mas as mulheres deste mundo, diz a anistia, querem cada vez mais: naidoo classificou 2018 "um ano marcado pela resistência das mulheres".
em seu prefácio, o ativista lembrou os protestos em todo mundo sob a hashtag #metoo contra a agressão sexual e a luta por justiça para milhares de mulheres na nigéria depois de ataques de soldados e extremistas do boko haram. na américa latina, um movimento feminino de proporções até então desconhecidas tomou as ruas sob o lema "ni una menos".
em alguns países, a situação das mulheres melhorou, como, por exemplo, na irlanda, onde o direito ao aborto foi liberalizado por referendo, ou na arábia saudita, onde as mulheres estão agora autorizadas a conduzir veículos.
leia mais neste post.

text:
tuesday truth bomb 💣 •
we are to have people in our lives that hold us accountable.  that help guide us into becoming the person god has created us to be, and when we waiver, they have a say so to confront us and set us straight. •

i’ve found too many people go without accountability.  they allow themselves to be isolated and to slide back into old ways and behaviors. •

we need to stop putting our church face on!! instead we need to be transparent with those we can trust and allow them to hold us accountable ! •

there is no beauty in hidden, wayward things. there is no growth in living carelessly.  there is no blessings, in isolation. •

live respectable, transparent and find people in your life to be able to hold you accountable to gods standards, not this worlds 🖤

xo

text:
. #noesno

sé que hay mil formas para decir sí; 
sé que hay silencios que hablan más que mil palabras 
que serán miradas que revelan lo que quiero, 
es vivir mi libertad. 
para frenar, para evitar sin explicarlo. 
no hay que ser sabio para comprender que… 
no es no, 
y hay una sola forma de decirlo, 
entiéndelo, no es no, 
y no hace falta que lo justifique 
cuando digo no es no, 
no tengo que gritarlo ni sentir vergüenza al decirlo, no. 
no es no, 
no importa si lo digo sonriendo o llorando, 
no es no, 
en cualquier idioma se comprende y queda claro, 
porque no es no, 
con una vez alcanza, no hace falta repetirlo, no es no. 
sé que hay distintos modos de sentir, 
sé que hay secretos que prefiero abrir al viento. 
eso es vivir sin miedo y poder elegir lo que quiero, 
es vivir mi libertad. 
para pensar, para callar sin explicarlo, 
no hay que ser sabio para comprender que… 
no es no, 
y hay una sola forma de decirlo, 
entiéndelo, no es no, 
y no hace falta que lo justifique 
cuando digo no es no, 
no tengo que gritarlo ni sentir vergüenza al decirlo, no. 
no es no, 
no importa si lo digo sonriendo o llorando, 
no es no, 
en cualquier idioma se comprende y queda claro, 
porque no es no, 
con una vez alcanza, no hace falta repetirlo, no es no. 
sé que hay mil formas para decir sí.
.
.
.
#noesno #yotecreo #miracomonosponemos
#metoo #girlpower

text:
covert narcissists are the most dangerous because their pathological lies make satan look like a bad liar. @regrann from @surviving_a_narc - this applies to my theme today about labeling people. what you see and hear are totallllyyyy different from what we experience from their horrific, blood-sucking years of calculated abuse. one can’t ever say, “it won’t happen to me!” because yes, sweetie. it can. sooo slowly they’ll begin kicking pebbles out from underneath you claiming they’re paving a smoother path. then it becomes the dirt. before you know it they’re literally digging you into their hole all the while telling you they’re just trying to keep you safe. getting out is seemingly impossible. this is why mislabeling is kind of a big deal...

text:
(swipe) bill cosby's lawyers on tuesday filed a list of nearly a dozen alleged trial errors as they appeal his sexual assault conviction and three- to 10-year prison term.

the defense asked to have the 81-year-old disgraced comedian released from a suburban #philadelphia prison while his appeal proceeds, but their pleas have so far been rejected.

the lawyers said trial judge steven o'neill had an alleged feud with a pretrial witness, the ex-prosecutor who had declined to charge cosby a decade earlier. and they said his decisions to preside over the case, let five other accusers testify, air cosby's prior deposition testimony about quaaludes and dismiss the ex-prosecutor's promise not to charge him are mistakes that warrant a new trial. "the trial court erred in failing to disclose his bias against district attorney (bruce) castor, and in failing to recuse himself, prior to determining (his) credibility," wrote lawyer brian perry, the latest of more than a dozen lawyers to represent cosby in the case.

a jury convicted cosby at a spring retrial of drugging and molesting a temple university employee in 2004, in what became the first celebrity trial of the #metoo era.

cosby — whose estimated fortune from his popular tv shows, comedy tours and product pitches once topped $400 million — was convicted of drugging and sexually assaulting accuser #andreaconstand. the entertainer, who is legally blind, spends his days in a one-man cell and private day room in a new state prison about 20 miles from his sprawling estate near #philadelphia, where the crime occurred.

in a deposition in constand's 2005 civil suit, cosby called the 2004 encounter consensual and his feelings for her romantic. constand considered him a mentor with close ties to her boss at #temple, where she worked for the women's basketball team. she was about 30 and cosby, a temple trustee, about 66 at the time. the key issues raised on appeal tuesday include: see below via hollywoodreporter  #billcosby #freebillcosby #farfromfinished

text:
#nonoscallamosmas

juan darthés denunciado por violación

el colectivo actrices argentinas se reunió hoy a las 19 hs en el multiteatro para acompañar a thelma fardín en su denuncia a juan darthés por violación 10 años atrás. “entendimos que estando juntas y organizadas nos multiplicabamos” fue parte del discurso de las actrices. 
alrededor de 400 actrices se reunieron hoy para acompañar y visibilizar las denuncias de compañeras que fueron víctimas de abuso sexual. en una conferencia de prensa, se denunció públicamente a juan darthés por violación en una gira en nicaragua hace 10 años, cuando thelma era menor de edad. la denuncia ya está en instancias judiciales pero hoy se dio a conocer el nombre de la víctima y del denunciado.

a partir del movimiento de actrices estadounidenses #metoo en hollywood, que terminó con la impunidad del productor harvey weinstein, acusado por abuso sexual, en argentina se desplegó el colectivo actrices argentinas. desde hace un tiempo se manifiestan en apoyo al movimiento feminista participando e impulsando actividades y movilizaciones a lo largo de todo el país. en este marco, varias actrices, conductoras y modelos comenzaron a denunciar y a hacer visibles episodios de violencia sufridas por colegas o compañeros en el ámbito laboral. “hoy decimos basta, se acabó. el tiempo de impunidad para los abusadores debe terminar” manifestaron las actrices.

#miracomonosponemos

a partir del movimiento de actrices estadounidenses #metoo en hollywood, que terminó con la impunidad del productor harvey weinstein, acusado por abuso sexual, en argentina se desplegó el colectivo actrices argentinas. desde hace un tiempo se manifiestan en apoyo al movimiento feminista participando e impulsando actividades y movilizaciones a lo largo de todo el país. en este marco, varias actrices, conductoras y modelos comenzaron a denunciar y a hacer visibles episodios de violencia sufridas por colegas o compañeros en el ámbito laboral. “hoy decimos basta, se acabó. el tiempo de impunidad para los abusadores debe terminar” manifestaron las actrices.

text: today was the final critique for my class this semester. this piece is supposed to be a small girl covered in hands, to bring attention to sexual abuse. surfacing this piece was...interesting. i attempted to do several washes of all different colors, but after the glaze firing it turned into a muddy throw up color. some things dont work out the way we plan. nevertheless, this little girl means a lot to me. she’s nowhere near perfect, but she is who she is. #ceramics #sculpture #metoo

text:
dear @robingwright: if i send this your way, will you autograph it and send it back? have your people get in touch with my people. please and thank you.
.
.
as some of you may recall, i shared a story about how i saw an infomercial on halloween day during the price is right.
.
.
that infomercial was for the president claire hale underwood commemorative plate. .
.
what was remarkable about the infomercial was the fact that it never mentioned it was a gag, nor that it was a promotional tool for the @netflix original series, @houseofcards. it was very funny, but very subtle. you had to be in on the joke.
.
.
i wound up calling the number in the infomercial a few of times. i was able to get through and leave a message with my name and callback number. about a week later, i received a call from mike with a & d fine classics (makers of this plate). i was told i had been awarded a plate. he took my name and address and informed me that the plate would be to me in 4 to 6 weeks.
.
.
guess what arrived today? .
.
i want to give my heartfelt thanks to netflix for this cherished piece of memorabilia. i am very appreciative. merry christmas to me!
.
.

text:
se que estas cansada, pero segui adelante. 
recien escuche el testimonio de violacion que vivio la actriz thelma fardin a manos de juan darthes. 
me acordaba de situaciones cotidianas, propias y ajenas que las mujeres vivimos a lo largo de nuestra vida. 
se lo que se siente ser abusada y no poder reaccionar, guardarlo en lo mas profundo de la psiquis hasta que el cuerpo empieza a “ hablar” mediante traumas y enfermedades. 
que no hay que decirlo, claro, porque no te creen, porque piensan que estas mintiendo. se lo que se siente. 
abrazo a esta chica y a tantas otras. 
#metoo #miracomonosponemos

text:
givers need to set limits because takers rarely do. – rachel wolchin
healthy boundaries are not walls to block others out. they are the gates and fences that allow you to enjoy the your own magnificent garden. they set us free in our garden to enjoy the beauty with those we love and most importantly with ourselves. 
i realize setting personal boundaries is so challenging to do (trust me!) because it’s saying that we have the courage to love ourselves despite the possibility of making someone angry or the fear of what someone will think of us.  when setting a boundary think about yourself.  and this isn’t being selfish, this is about self-care.  if we don’t set boundaries and hold people accountable then we end up feeling mistreated.  saying no is an option and it’s ok to set limits. you are responsible for your happiness.  love yourself and the beauty of your garden because you’re worth it.  xo

text:
cw: sexual assault. for a very long time i’ve gone back and forth on sharing this because i have coped with this trauma by dissociating with it, by looking at the things that have happened to me in the past as happening to not me, but young dumb laura who didn’t know any better, and just needs a hug. which like i said is not me, so why tell anyone in my life about it- so they can only see that every time they look at me, no thanks because i don’t want to be known as a rape victim or a rape survivor,  actually i don’t even want to be associated with anything rape at all, because that’s not me, what happened to me doesn’t make up me, it’s not even a part of me, but whether i like it or not it’s something impossibly heavy that i’ll carry with me for the rest of my life. 
i recorded this video about just one of the times i was sexually assaulted a couple months ago when i was drunk (another great coping mechanism 🙄)and alone because at the time i had no one to talk to about this because i have made it that way. i’ve finally decided to share this video to maybe help someone in a similar situation see they too are not alone, and don’t need to live in this while they carry it all by themselves, but i am also sharing this video more importantly after just reading about the texas judge who let the baylor frat president go free with no consequences after drugging and raping a 19 year old at a frat party. so maybe someone will see it, and understand the gravity of their actions before they permanently damage another human’s soul for good because they have been taught their whole life by our society that they are entitled or have the right to do so. #metoo #ibelieveher #youarenotalone you are both disgusting monsters #judgeralphstrother #jacobwalteranderson #rapist

text:
recomendaciones | navidades libres de #asi 🎄 
1.- expliquemos a nuestros hijos dónde y con quién van a quedarse. también identifiquemos el o los periodos de permanencia fuera de casa recordándoles las formas de ponerse en contacto con nosotros.

2.- asegurémonos que nuestros hijos aprendan de memoria nuestro número de contacto personal, e indiquemos que pueden llamarnos si se sienten amenazados. garanticemos que podremos atender su llamada en cualquier momento.

3.- practiquemos con ellos contraseñas familiares que puedan decirnos, para avisarnos que se sienten amenazados, sin generar alarma en el medio donde se encuentra. #navidadesseguras

text:
this is one of my highlight pieces of my ap art concentration. this was based of a smaller drawing that i made, but decided to make it bigger and portfolio ready. the words in this drawing are based off my personal experiences with sexual assault and abuse. i’ve been through some very toxic relationships recently and have been called every single word seen above, carved into my body. (and that wasn’t even the extent of what was said to me.) it taught me a great lesson about knowing when to leave and knowing the warning signs. i decided to take my struggles and turn them into something greater, a piece of art that will hopefully resonate with others who have experienced something like this. ❤️

- not having private dinners with a female, especially when there is fear of flirtation - not sitting next to females on a plane or train
- not traveling on business meetings alone with a female
- avoiding any type of potentially problematic interactions with a female... well, i guess all that's left, after the rules of khalwa, mahram, safar, and others have already been put into place, is to don appropriate clothes for men and women *cough* hijab *cough*, and...voila! we will have an islamically compliant work-place!

text:
✨sara danius ✨
kirjallisuustieteen professori
valittiin 2015 ensimmäisenä naisena ruotsin akatemian sihteeriksi. keväällä danius erosi akatemiasta parin kollegansa kanssa petyttyään sen kykenemättömyyteen ratkaista akatemian sisäistä #metoo-kohua. ✨
daniuksesta kirjoitettiin eilen pääasiassa nobel-juhlassa käyttämänsä asunsa vuoksi, joka surullista kyllä uutisvirrassa sai minunkin klikkaukseni. on välillä hurjaa seurata uutisointia naisten pukeutumisen ympärillä ja huomata omia huonoja ajatusmalleja niitä lukiessa. olen kuitenkin toiveikas, sillä jokainen lukemani juttu ja postaus daniuksen asusta sisälsivät myös maininnan keväisestä #metoo kohusta ja mimmin merkityksestä koko kampanjan puolestapuhujana. veitolan postausta kompaten on upeaa nähdä miten muoti voi olla osana politiikkaa ja esimerkiksi tässä tapauksessa yksi keino saada hyvien toimittajien käsissä palstatilaa tärkeille ja ajankohtaisille aiheille.👗

text:
did you know that the restaurant industry reports more sexual harassment claims than any other industry in the us? this is one of the biggest issues facing our business & it’s time to have an honest, gender-inclusive conversation about what we can do to change behaviors that have been accepted for too long.
.
meet the panelists who will be adding their voices to “work after #metoo” - our facebook live event where we will tackle this topic, happening tomorrow (dec. 12) from 3-4pm:
.
- cristina perez, outreach director of @woarphila
- chelsea edwards, attorney from @justiceatwork
- calvin okunyoe, program coordinator from @roc_united
- natalia nicastro, from #philaposh
- symbol lai, from @cityofphiladelphia mayor’s office of immigrant affairs
- chef maria campbell, founder of @cookswhocare
.
join us to share your perspective & to ask the questions everyone should be asking, even if you were afraid to ask before. it’s easy! click the link in our bio to be added to the cooks who care community facebook group, where this live event is taking place.
.
.
.
#cookswhocare #panel #discussion #opendialogue #management #modernmanagement #inclusivity #leadership #becausewecare #supportsurvivors #educate #endsexualviolence #hopeendures  #philadelphia #accesstojustice

text:
меган фокс объяснила, почему не поддержала движение #metoo, хотя была жертвой харассмента.

когда звезды голливуда объявляли войну домогательствам в киноиндустрии и друг за другом рассказывали о том, как страдали от харассмента, актриса меган фокс не была замечена на передовой движения #metoo. в недавнем разговоре с корреспондентом new york times 32-летняя звезда "трансформеров" ( transformers) объяснила, почему так произошло.

актриса не стала детально описывать случаи домогательств в своей жизни, но при этом заявила, что их было предостаточно. фокс пожаловалась, что еще до массового всплеска общественного негодования выступала против подобного отношения к женщине, но получила разочарование: ее никто не поддержал.

оглядываясь назад, когда меня не поддержали феминистки и другие представители общества, я не верила, что ко мне отнесутся с сочувствием… сейчас общество одобряет качества и проявления личности, из-за которых раньше все отвернулись от меня,
— пояснила она в интервью.

ранее меган сравнивала режиссера "трансформеров" майкла бэйя с гитлером и говорила, что образ ее героини в фильме чересчур сексуален.

дома актрису окружают одни мужчины — с мужем брайаном остином грином она воспитывает троих сыновей. по словам фокс, она часто размышляет о правильном воспитании мальчиков.

для сыновей я — окно в мир противоположного пола. если они чувствуют себя в безопасности рядом со мной, то так же будут чувствовать себя и с другими женщинамив в перспективе. если они будут видеть, что их отец уважаем меня, то примут норму такого поведения,
— сказала меган  new york times.

text:
este makeup lo hice desde mi pequeño lugar como maquilladora, en color  #naranja y con mucho #amor para apoyar los "16 días activismo contra la violencia de género". esta es una campaña internacional de lucha contra la violencia hacia mujeres y niñas, iniciada en 1991 a propuesta del centro para el liderazgo global de mujeres y desde 2008 apoyada por naciones unidas. el tema de este año es: pinta el mundo de naranja! #escúchametambién 
es importante que tomemos conciencia y colaboremos desde la educación y el respeto, para que eliminemos todos y cualquier tipo de comportamiento que implique violencia hacia una mujer o niña. las y los activistas entienden que si bien los nombres y los contextos pueden variar en función de los distintos lugares geográficos, las mujeres y las niñas de todo el mundo sufren maltratos generalizados y sus historias deben salir a la luz. educá con amor, ayudá y se parte del cambio. #dino #noviolencia #niunamenos #metoo  #yotambién #timesup  #niunamenos #notonemore #balancetonporc #mujeres #nacionesunidas #activismo #makeup #makeupartist #makeuplover #makeupargentina #maquillajeprofesional #maquillajeargentina #makeuptutorial #makeupvideos  #makeupbyromiz #maquillaje

text:
#ruok ?¿?¿?¿?¿? saddness is a terrible reality.. its a heaviness you carry deep within your heart that almosts suffocates you..this is where crying comes in handy..it releases the pressure of those clenched emotions you have carried for how ever long you have..for me its a daily struggle im on a journey learning these emotions of life and how they do effect me so i can try and make them better.. please to my friends and family i would appreciate your understanding that mental illness comes in many shapes and forms..many people including myself do have daily struggles and it is while we have supportive people who dont make judgement of us that we thrive the most...everyday all we wish....is to feel normal what ever that may be.. i know many suffer in silence and some like myself we scream and shout lol but please dont be affraid to ask those few words even to a stranger u may see in distress.. r u ok???? it may make all the difference xoxox today im mostly ok.. i hope you are too. xoxox thanks for listening 😘 never feel alone as there is always someone who understands because they struggle too...life is hard and for those who struggle with mental illness it is even harder.. #ruok
#ruok 
#wearmyshoes

text:
alla ni på marknaden i söndags som ville skicka den här bilden till era mammor som julkort(eller till andra badass människor) -ja fixar! dma så postar jag till dom direkt med valfri handskriven liten hälsning! begränsat antal har några kvar!
.
kreativa textförslag:
"du och jag mamma slå in #inteallamän™ i plastpaket vid floden i jul? hör av dig, jag väntar. puss, din dotter."
.
"fuck you tomten - women unite!"
.
"#inteallamän™ men alla jävla tomtar."
.
"backaallabrudar"
.
"systraskapet älskar dig! god jul!"
.
"eat sleep fuck the patriarchy repeat"
.
"julstämning röd som mans och mensblod på gatorna!"
.
"ri♀t"
.
"du är min gröt mamma."
.
"dumpa din kille mamma, sen pappa -god fortsättning! /din dotter"
.
okreativa men ok förslag:
du är fantastisk, älskar dig, pusspusspussgodjul etc etc eget val ni väljer! .
kostnad totalt med frakt 75 swishade kronor! begränsat antal!
.
god jul önskar @ester_sot

text:
very interesting letter from @ucobronchos president today. i hope these new policies are enacted and actually enforced.

these policies definitely were not enforced when i filed multiple harassment claims and my harasser was allowed to keep his job even after admitting to harassing me and threatening to assault me on multiple occasions. that same man was able to continue harassing me for over a year until, after suffering from weekly, sometimes daily panic attacks, i had to leave my job. 
yup. you read that correctly.

for the sake of all women (and men) still on the @ucobronchos campus and those that will be there in the future, i truly hope title ix is taken seriously in the future. 
#metoo

text:
#worldhumanrightsday
#worldhumanrights 
so yesterday was world human rights day.  i'm a day late to the party.  better late than never especially when it's for an issue close to my heart.

the theme for 2018 is #standupforhumanrights

here's to standing up to all forms of xenophobia, standing up against poverty, and standing up for political, civil, economic, social and cultural rights ✊🏽 i'm not a huge fan of social media but one thing it has been is drawn attention to the ills in our world.  this year the focus has rightly been on gender equality with #metoo ,  a spotlight on police killings of black communities and in particular young black men in the us by @kaepernick7 @childishgambino to name but a few and the right for trans equality by our very own @munroebergdorf

god told us the greatest commandment is love and we should "love our neighbours like we love ourselves". this certainly would be one step towards healing the world and making it a better place.  love surely can make the world go round 💞 🌍

#humanrights 
#humanrace 
#humanrightsforall 
#humanrightsaremypride 
#humanitarian
#humankind 
#lovecanmaketheworldgoround 
#loveisfire 
#loveismyreligion
#loveiseverything 
#godislove
name: Yvonne Nakuze 🇰🇪🇺🇬🇬🇧

text:
estamos complacidos de haber apoyado la campaña 16 días de activismo contra la violencia de género, que se realizó desde el pasado 25 de noviembre, día internacional de la eliminación de la violencia contra la mujer, hasta el 10 de diciembre, día de los derechos humanos.

desde las ciudades de san cristóbal en táchira y guasdualito en apure, participamos en diversas celebraciones, programadas junto a otras ong y organismos públicos, para brindar atención y orientación psicológica a casos de violencia sexual basada en género e impulsar actividades recreativas y culturales para promover el sano esparcimiento y la convivencia pacífica.
.
.
.

text:
alia shawkat is an actress and an activist, who has started in saving grace, and arrested development. after acting for many years, she coproduced a movie called ‘duck butter’, a film that she also stars in. the movie revolves around the relationship between two women, but shawkat emphasizes that she tiptoes around the boundaries of a “gay film”. she mentions that the purpose of the movie was to explore the vulnerability in relationships. 
she has also been intentional in speaking up in support of the #metoo survivors, especially after the allegation against jeffrey tambor came out. 
shawkat inspires me because of her ability to act so vulnerable on camera. in her movie, ‘duck butter’, they filmed the movie in real time. she wanted to portray a type of relationship that had yet to be portrayed through film that she had never seen before, so she produced the film that she (and her co-producer miguel arteta, wanted to.

intervention de l’humoriste noemie de lattre qui nous explique la difficulté de sensibiliser sur les violences faites aux femmes. la cause reste encore peu soutenue, il faut donc continuer à alerter l’opinion publique sur les ravages des violences faites aux femmes.
noemie de lattre : suivez les prochaines dates de son spectacle « feministe pour homme » prévues pour février 2019. artiste punchy et drôle à découvrir absolument !! 👏🏽💪🏽

text:
jacob walter anderson, now 23, was given a $400 fine, a recommended three years’ probation and ongoing psychological, alcohol and substance abuse counseling. the victim, identified as #donnadoe in court records, said the ex-phi delta theta fraternity president anderson drugged and repeatedly raped her at a #fraternity party when she was a 19-year-old sophomore. #anderson was originally indicted on four counts of sexual assault, and faced two to 20 years in prison and a $10,000 fine. in october, anderson was offered a controversial plea deal for a lesser charge of unlawful restraint. the woman said she felt disoriented after accepting a drink she thought contained punch at a 2016 fraternity house party at #bayloruniversity. she said anderson led her behind a tent and repeatedly raped her while she was gagged and choked.

a warrant said the woman was assaulted until she lost consciousness and anderson left her alone. the warrant said she had vomited on herself and could have choked to death in the backyard. 
the judge’s decision monday is not the first time that judge ralph #strother has allowed such lenient punishment for #sexcrimes. last year, he sentenced a man to deferred probation after he pleaded guilty in the 2013 rape of a former #baylor student. the judge ordered the man to pay for the woman’s counseling. the man told police the woman had been drunk, according to an affidavit. >>this judge should be kicked off the bench. you’d think it was #kavanaugh rendering judgement in this case ——————————————————-#rapeculture #rapecultureisreal #grossmiscarriageofjustice  #metoo #timesup #sexualassault #rape

text:
après le sketch de noémie de lattre, voici le discours de clôture de la soirée « les invincibles » par mme frédérique martz : cofondatrice & directrice générale de l’institut women safe. elle est aussi membre de la clef (coordination française pour le lobby européen des femmes), du réseau mission locale des yvelines, et membre du réseau association femme médecin libéral (fml). bravo et merci pour cette belle soirée d’échanges et de sensibilisation sur les ravages des violences sur les victimes ainsi que sur le sujet de l’excision 👏🏽🙏🏽.

text_retweet:
kindly keep me anonymous. 
it's gotten too far and i can't take it anymore yet i can't leave him. our wedding is going to be six years this december, it all started during our courtship when he was overly jealous and sensitive to words even when i was just playing but i didn't pay much attention to it as i felt the jealousy was due to his love for me but it grew worse after we got married, i had my first miscarriage when he beat me black and blue just because he saw me being dropped off by a friend i ran into at the mall and ever since then the beating never stopped and it always due to one excuse or the other but at the end of it all, i'm always the one at fault and each time after he's calm he always come begging with lots of gift just for me to forgive saying he does everything  due to the love he has for me, i can't leave him cause he's the one paying for my parents house rent and he has promised to throw them out if i ever leave him. the worst happened yesterday when he beat me in front of our friends and made me loose yet another baby claiming i'm sleeping with our next-door neighbor, i'm currently at the hospital while i type this and it's all so overwhelming, he owns everything i own and if i leave him, i loose it all

the gorgeous marzana rahman
please support this amazing lady who is on a mission to raise awareness of domestic violence that affects women daily! every 30 seconds police get a call from a woman in distress. its time to act, time to raise our voices and say no!!!!! no to violence, no to abuse, no to looking away and hiding bruises. just say no!!!! all i ask is £5. we spend that on junk. please help to make a difference. every penny from this fund will go to the women of rohingya. living with babies and children in filthy camps. no solid structutes permitted so only plastic to shelter them. is this right? is this just? is this the world we live in??? help marzana fight. stand by her and lets get our voices heard. its christmas...if you are celebrating...please buy one more gift and donate whatever you can. if you are not....then please donate and think of it as your good deed of the day. we waste money on so much. lets gift someone a little comfort to their miserable lives. we all have kids. we all have daughters....what we do now will lead to a better future for them. support @brokenbrides on social media and support @marzana.rahman  open up your hearts and please
please share to all your contacts and on your pages. may god by whatever name you know him by bless you and your family. ameen 😊

text:
so me! 😁😀🤩❤ i needed a little vacay from using my brain for anything other than getting through the day! 😐

sorry for any dms, comments, likes or follows i've not responded to...shit got real & i've been trying too process stuff in my messy little mind😶🙄😏🤦‍♀️... but...i'm on it...i have goals, a plan, a positive mindset & more importantly than that... nothing has ever stopped me yet... and nothing ever will! 🙅‍♀️ my mind, body & spirit are stronger than anything they have had to endure💪🤛🧠❤
and so are yours🙏 whatever you have been through, it hasn't beaten you, remember that if you ever doubt yourself 🤗

text:
“you are stronger than you think”
20x20” acrylic, nov 2017
.
i’ve kept all the notes that i’ve used as paintings (unless they were commissioned). this one i wrote out, tore,  rolled up, then sat there for at least an hour rubbing that note as if it was a form of therapy.  i was at a conference, so there was probably a couple sessions of me sitting there with the note in my hands until the edges began to fray. .

even the strongest of people still need the gentlest reminders (of truth). . 
maybe i say this every time, but this is one of my favorites.  those push pins and shadows 😍🤤. .

text: store update!!! now all my series des hommes et fleurs prints are available in my store!!! 👉🏻 caracarmina.com (link on bio) / this series of #vintagephotos with #digitalillustration talks about how women keep silent and pretend to be happy.  all the women in these series are #burlesquedancers or #theateractresses from the 30’s and 40’s.  at the time they were considered to be the most liberated ones but the sad truth is that behind the stage courtains they had little freedom and most were being paid less than their male counterparts and some were even treated horribly by the men around them.  hoping we all stop being silent and can live our lives as we decide! i hope we all can shout together and be free! 🌺 ••• #caracarmina #contemporarycollage #collage #mixedmedia #blackandwhitephotography #feminist #womenempowerment #feminism #fleurs #flowers #womenrights #illustration #theimportantthings #photointervention #40swomen #30swomen #40s #30s #contemporaryart #collage #womenart #femme #mujer #metoo #speakup #stopthesilence #feministart

text:
i want to share this is a very sad story but important story. the push to expose this awful behavior by buddhist project sunshine is applauded and appreciated.

here is the link (sorry i do not have live links in my feed as this is very long. there are lots of articles if you use the search criteria buddhist project sunshine.

https://thinkprogress.org/colorado-police-investigating-alleged-sexual-assaults-by-buddhist-leaders-d5374c4f702d/?fbclid=iwar3ecwndeulk2fwfjzslupdzkqmv0xm5knvcdnpixf6rtfbnbly1mixpt4g

i have seen this happen in many communities now. bikram, anuasara, rigpa, diamond mountain…

jetsunma tenzin palmo taught me to separate the teachings from the teacher and showed me that, consistent in all buddhist teachings, are valuable guidelines for finding authentic teachers. (easy to find but let me know if you want a list)

i can’t say that i am not dissolutioned by the hierarchical, patriarchal, feudal systems of tibetan buddhism and that i don’t struggle with the desire to ‘throw the baby out with the bath water’. i can say that my 25+ year meditation practice has been the strongest foundation and support of my life and humbly state that it has provided me with as discerning wisdom i strive to unfold daily.

i am so interested in how others work with this fucked-up-ness. 
any comments are appreciated.

#metoo, #justice, #religion, #sakyong mipham, #sexual assault, #shambhala #shambhalametoo #discerningwisdom

text:
in 2014, steve bannon – then executive chairman of the “alt-right” news network breitbart – was christopher wylie’s boss. and robert mercer, the secretive us hedge-fund billionaire and republican donor, was cambridge analytica’s investor. and the idea they bought into was to bring big data and social media to an established military methodology – “information operations” – then turn it on the us electorate.

cambridge analytica’s parent company, scl, had won contracts with the us state department and was pitching to the pentagon, and wylie was genuinely freaked out. - it’s insane, he told me one night. - the company has created psychological profiles of 230 million americans. and now they want to work with the pentagon? it’s like nixon on steroids.

carole cadwalladr
the guardian

text: acoso, abuso, violación y violencia machista son huella en la cuerpa de mujeres actrices en espacios que se comparten desde el quehacer laboral y no está de más decir que ser actriz ó profe de teatro en el interior del país es un camino de hormiga soñadora difícil que elegimos porque nos llena el alma. hoy a las 19hs habrá una conferencia de prensa desde actrices argentinas, verán muchas caras de buenos aires caba nosotras las teatreras de otras provincias también acompañamos porque estamos unidas en este camino de estar cerca, de cuidarnos, de terminar con el miedo ó esperar a que nos den mayor o menor credibilidad cuando sufrimos violencia, por un sin fin de escusas horrorosas. estamos organizadas y desde que sabemos que estamos juntas nos vamos a encargar de que en nuestros espacios de creación se repudie, se condene y se haga eco de lo que nuestras huellas gritan. no vamos a permitir estos atropellos, no tenemos miedo y somos la voz de las que callaron. le decimos no a la violencia machista #actricesposadas #actricesmisiones #actricesposadasmisiones #colectivaactricesautoconvocadasmisiones #colectivaactricesautoconvocadasposadasmisiones @actricesmisiones @actricesargentinas #metoo #miracomonosponemos #lovamosatirar #hermanayositecreo #calladasnuncamás #nuncamastendranlacomodidaddenuestrosilencio #miracomonosponemos #noesno #nonoscallamosnuncamas

text:
el periodista saudí asesinado jamal khashoggi, junto con otros tres reporteros y un medio de comunicación, fueron designados hoy como persona del año 2018 por la revista time. -
“este año estamos reconociendo cuatro periodistas y un medio de comunicación que han pagado un terrible precio por encarar los desafíos de este momento", indicó edward felsenthal, director de la publicación neoyorquina, en un comunicado.
-
junto khashoggi, también fueron destacados la periodista filipina maria ressa, editora del portal de noticias rappler, muy crítico con el presidente filipino, rodrigo duterte; y los reporteros de la agencia reuters wa lone y kyaw soe oo, detenidos por las autoridades de birmania mientras investigaban las atrocidades cometidas contra la minoría rohingya.
-
asimismo, el periódico local capital gazette, de annapolis (maryland), donde cinco reporteros resultaron muertos en un tiroteo este año.

text:
sex after abuse: part 2/3 ❤️ what to do about the panic?
.
2 things are critical here: your relationship with yourself and your relationship with the other. both are equally important. there are certainly ways you can help yourself, but ultimately this will be resolved with an intimate partner (even if they don't realise this).
.
for all aspects of healing and living again, including sex, i have found from both my personal experience and my research that the key is the body. trauma is registered in the body, changing its neurobiology and physiology, and disconnecting it from the self, living its own reality. so, of course, as sex is such an intimate bodily experience, it can be extremely frightening and triggering - and even more so when the #trauma comes from #sexualabuse. naturally, many can experience extreme panic, or worse (reliving or re-traumatisation, for ex.).
.
luckily, sex can also be healing! not simply the act, but the intimate connection with your own body and the intimate connection with another person. it is intra- and inter-relational connection in a context of safety that enables the healing of trauma and the growth post-trauma. of course, this doesn't happen just through sex, sex isn't an option for everyone and it doesn't have to be, and most importantly it never means you should push yourself to have sex. but if the conditions and timing are right, sex can be one part of the building of your relationship with yourself and with others.
.
there are a few persons who have been key in my healing, for different reasons (and some also who have hindered it). there is one person who was incredibly important without knowing it. at the time, i was confused, scared, and disgusted. but one day, i met someone for whom i felt immense attraction. a natural, beautiful, instantaneous attraction. by being drawn to him, i was drawn out of my trauma - not fully, but enough to embody something that was entirely out of trauma's realm. something strong and real. i won't share the whole story, but overall he was a big part of my reconnection with myself, with my body, with my sensations, and with my emotions. 🦋
.
.
#metoo

text:
la violencia contra las mujeres y las niñas es una de las violaciones de los derechos humanos más graves, extendidas, arraigadas y toleradas en el mundo.

a nivel global, 1 de cada 3 mujeres ha sufrido violencia física y/o sexual a lo largo de su vida, y en algunos países esta proporción aumenta a 7 de cada 10.

este año bajo el lema #escúchametambién, las naciones unidas reconocen la determinación, relevancia y valentía de activistas y movimientos en defensa de las sobrevivientes de violencia, tales como #metoo, #miprimeracoso, #timesup, y #niunamenos, y hacen un llamado para que todas las estrategias que se implementen para erradicar la violencia contra las mujeres y las niñas, desde todos los sectores, sean integrales.

para alcanzar los objetivos de la agenda 2030 de desarrollo sostenible debemos:
•atender las causas estructurales de la violencia contra las mujeres y las niñas desde sus raíces, lo que implica la necesidad de tomar acción para la prevención.
•promover marcos normativos y de política pública que sean integrales; que tengan perspectiva de género y de interculturalidad; con enfoque de derechos humanos, en cumplimiento de los más altos estándares internacionales, y que sean efectivamente implementados.
•fortalecer a las instituciones estatales, así como a la sociedad civil, en sus mecanismos de coordinación para prevenir, atender, sancionar y erradicar la violencia contra las mujeres y las niñas y con recursos suficientes para esta tarea.
•generar información estadística y evidencia que se encuentren alineados a estándares internacionales en la materia, para crear normas, políticas públicas que prevengan y atiendan adecuadamente la violencia contra las mujeres y las niñas.
•proveer servicios accesibles de calidad para la atención de víctimas de violencia; servicios de salud y de procuración e impartición de justicia con estándares internacionales.
🎀necesitamos un movimiento global para poner fin a todas las formas de violencia hacia las mujeres y niñas, así que fortalezcamos a los movimientos que buscan sacar a la luz y poner bajo un reflector este tipo de violencia.

recuerda, el verdadero cambio inicia contigo✨!

text:
sometimes, in just the right light, it’s as though i have a butt 🙌✨ and that’s what yoga is all about folks 😌 swipe right for a weird shape 🤔🤨 •
•
since the #metoo movement, i’ve spent a great deal of time thinking about sexism. initially i felt frustrated by the behavior of women who i perceived were utilizing the movement in a way that actually set women back, and encouraged benevolent sexism. •
•
i then became aware that i, too, exhibited sexist biases and supported benevolent sexism. this latter kind, as the title implies, isn’t overt, hostile discrimination; but it is insidious, and its existence is correlated with the repression of women’s rights. •
•
this, amidst a current, ongoing conversation about ‘the sexualization of yoga’, specifically on instagram. i felt frustrated seeing people practicing provocative asanas in skimpy clothing, but seemingly denying that they were using their bodies to promote themselves. i was also irked that regardless of a woman’s intentions, they were accused of ‘sexualizing yoga’, with the accuser taking zero responsibility for their perception. •
•
once it dawned on me that i’ve exhibited (do exhibit) this behavior as well (and that women apparently lose no matter what they do 🙄) it became easier to accept this potential behavior in others. my wish is that people start to take accountability on either side. if i’m benefitting from benevolent sexism but then object to other forms of discrimination because they don’t *benefit me*, that’s hypocritical. if i as the beholder perceive sexual manipulation, that’s *my* perception. i can’t force anyone else to take accountability for themselves, their thoughts, their feelings or actions; but i can acknowledge my own hypocrisy, anti-social tendencies and implicit bias. 
continued in comments >>

text:
where's the #metoo movement at for his accusers. 
jeffrey epstein did have to register as a sexual offender, but mainly just had to apologize to the attorney, not even a word to the victims, it's cases like epstein’s that don’t just hurt the victims, they undermine the legitimacy of the entire justice system. for six years, between 2001 and 2007, jeffrey epstein ran a sex trafficking ring that preyed on minor girls as young as 13. so why was he given a slap on the wrist by federal prosecutors in florida? senators, both republican and democrat, are asking the same question. now senators are calling for the doj’s inspector general to review the handling of the case as well as for a congressional review of the “decision-making” process. 🇺🇸 #pedowood #maga #dabs #qanon #undergroundatelier #fullspectrum #fitness #710 #sativa #indica #420 #cryptocurrency #organic #weed #dab #entrepreneur #health #design #cbd #development

text:
bienvenu chez les ch’tis ! 
j’avais dû quitter lille en 2002 après mon dut « tech’ de co’ 1998» lassée des enchainements de missions intérim sans intérêt alors que mon diplôme était sensé être un « passeport » pour un début de carrière dans la banque ou les assurances. quel dommage 😥 
donc j’avais dit ; bye bye le nord pour une « new life in paris ». à la place suis devenue...assistante de direction trilingue 🇫🇷🇬🇧🇪🇸
donc pour résumer : quand on a traversé des rues pendant 4ans pour se voir proposer des emplois différents de celui qu’on voulait exercer par ses études...bah on traverse l’autoroute a1  lille >paris mdr 😂 🏃🏾‍♀️🏃🏾‍♀️🚗
bref retour à lille et sa grand place :
souvenirs, souvenirs....🤔... #chtis #bienvenuchezleschtis #nordpasdecalais #lille 
#womensrights #womensrightsarehumanrights #humanrightsforall #womensrightsday #noustoutes #noustoutesharcelement #noustoutes2411 #respect #dignity #dignityforall #dignitepourtous #dignite #droitshumainspourtous #metoo #metoomovement #metoomovement2018 #allhumanshaverights #ensemblecontrelesviolences #25novembregiornatamondialecontrolaviolenzasulledonne #25denoviembrediainternacionalcontralaviolenciadegenero #25novembremaipiu #25novemberinternationaldayfortheeliminationofviolenceagainstwomen #25novembre #25novembresempre #25novembre2018

text:
whilst today marks the 10th of december, otherwise known a
#internationalhumanrightsday it also marks the end of #16daysofactivism.

it is difficult to fully celebrate #humanrightsday because womens rights have not yet been fully recognized, yet womens rights are in fact human rights.

whilst we have flooded your screens and whilst we have been flooded with stats and facts about gender based violence, domestic violence, intimate partner violence, rape, femicide, female genital mutilation, the psychological, social and economic abuse of women and girls, and so much more we must remember that we have barely even scratched the surface.

the number of unreported cases still remains unknown in all these forms of violence metted out against women, womxn and girls. whilst we hope that this countdown has been informative & will help equip you with more tools to fight these societal illls we know we have not covered nearly enough. more stats and facts can be seen from @legalaidsa1 as well as further understanding the process for getting protection orders is also covered in the domestic violence act in south africa.

information on possible shelters that might be able to assist you can be found on http://www.gauteng.gov.za/services/women/pages/shelters.aspx whilst these aren't the only shelters they are a start.

the countdown might have ended but the struggle continues. let's continue to #orangetheworld

with you in revolutionary spirit -  blackwomxncaucus

text: on a monday night in midtown #manhattan, a group of approximately 20 men were baring their #souls. “i’m angry that my health is deteriorating. i’m not ready to be an old man,” said jeff nichols who’s 70. ranging in age from 30 to 70, the men were gathered as part of the @themankindproject (mkp), a 33-year-old nonprofit with 24 chapters in the u.s. and 11 regions abroad. it focuses on things like men’s emotional well-being, drawing on elements like carl jung’s theories of the psyche, nonviolent communication, breath work and native american customs. men, who are less likely than women to seek out individual therapy, are increasingly looking for outlets in this fraught cultural moment of political acrimony, widespread economic instability and major societal reckoning over their behavior. at mkp, membership is at an all-time high and enrollment is up 8% over the last year, said boysen hodgson, the director of marketing and communications. “with time’s up now and #metoo, many men know they have to be more accountable,” boysen said. “a lot of them are saying, ‘i don’t want that to be me. i don’t want that to be how #men are seen in the world.’” @caseykelbaugh took this photo during an mkp weekly meeting in manhattan. visit the link in our profile to read more.
name: The New York Times

text:
sabina habla: el odio de nuestros nombres.

taroob significa casada. abla, perfectamente formada. afaf es castidad y aroob se puede traducir como amante de su esposo. arub significa dedicada a su marido. ashia es la esposa favorita de mohamed. si pasamos a la b encontramos buthayna que es de hermoso y ofrecido cuerpo. imthithal es obediencia y abda, significa esclava. 
éstas que enumero aquí no son solo palabras árabes. son nombres. nombres de mujer.
en occidente, hasta 1979 los nombres que se le ponían a todas las tormentas que devastaban el planeta eran siempre de mujer.

text:
— a former baylor university student indicted on four counts of sexual assault won't spend a single day in prison, according to local reports.
instead, a plea agreement allowed jacob walter anderson, an ex-fraternity president, to plead no contest to a lesser charge of unlawful restraint, cnn affiliate kwtx reported.
if the 24-year-old successfully completes three years of deferred probation and pays a $400 fine, his criminal record will be wiped clean of the charge, and he won't have to register as a sex offender, cnn affiliate kwkt said.
the plea agreement between anderson's defense team and the mclennan county, texas, district attorney's office infuriated the victim and her attorney. meanwhile former sex-slave; 16 year old #cyntoiabrown was sentenced by the tennessee supreme court to 50+ years for killing her abuser in an attempt to save her own life. in a constitutional; democratic society how does regional #jurisprudence play a role as its very strange how justices and judges from the southern; more conservative states reason on cases verses those of the north with a more liberal mindset. it often comes off as a racial; socioeconomic trade off where the more privileged you are, the more likely you’re going to have a criminal case swayed in your favor particularly in states like georgia, tennessee, texas and florida among others. both cases mentioned above deal with sexual assault; both have evidence of sex abuse: one l with the abuser walking free because he was privileged to obtain a plea deal and the other sentenced to spend the rest of her life in prison for escaping her rapist(s) by taking her abusers life. with all this talk of #metoo and #timesup it appears the courts are keeping up with their tradition of ignoring society and the media and drifting off into their own world where legality and common sense don’t always add up...

text:
📰 #coveteur : #antoniathomas talks landing a huge tv role and tackling career anxiety
plus, her little trick to memorizing lines.
🔴@coveteur : is this role [ #drclairebrowne on #thegooddoctor ] important to you personally?
🔵 @althomas1 : “the show is a vessel. it’s interesting because it’s obviously highlighting autism as a condition, and the positive side of it. people with autism can do very wonderful things. also, i’ve never played a young professional woman who has got her shit together, essentially. i think what’s so amazing about this role is that since season one, she’s been put through the rigmarole as a professional, like having killed someone by mistake as a doctor, which actually kind of blows my mind and is something you don’t ever think about when you think about surgeons. there were a few episodes where we tackled sexual harassment in the workplace. it was kind of crazy when that episode came out, because it was just around the time of the #metoo movement and that all exploding. the writers wrote this before it happened, it was really weird. but i was then able to explore that, which is such a gift and so important to be a voice at that time. and i’m really excited about what’s coming up for the character. many more obstacles, sort of being assertive and learning how to be assertive and be a strong woman in the workplace without being labeled a bitch. which is really exciting.”
✏: #katiebecker
📷: #aleckugler

text:
there's a powerful reason to call ourselves "survivors" over "victims." victimhood locks your mind in a state of powerlessness. and even worse, you believe you will never get past the pain and the trauma and the life-altering consequences that come with being a victim.
.
when you are sexually assaulted or wronged in any other way that causes damage to your personhood, your mind is thrown into this state. it's unfair. it's absolutely never deserved or justified. it's quite plainly a violation of your human rights. but, eventually, you have to stop calling yourself a victim and start calling yourself a survivor.
.
you have to be the person to initiate the climb out of the victim state of mind.
.
you have to be the person to decide you want to heal, and that healing is a long, difficult, and tumultuous process that never happens linearly.
.
and nobody else can tell you to make your mind transition from victim to survivor. you decide when you're ready to make that happen. but, it has to happen at some point for you to be able to find happiness and health in this one life– the only life that we know for sure.
.
changes to the institutions that neglect us cannot begin to make necessary changes until we rise above victim status and begin to call ourselves survivors instead. and we are survivors. to be able to resiliently rise above the pain and trauma, not just once but as many times as it resurfaces throughout our lifetimes –that's surviving.
.
when we realize we can survive our traumas is when we can begin to find our voices again. that's when we must start coming forward, boldly and unapologetically, to call out those responsible for the neglect of our human rights.
.
and if you haven't been able to find your voice, i will always be here to speak on behalf of survivors. please reach out if you ever need a listening ear or even a storyteller to help you feel heard.
-
#sexualassault #sexualassaultsurvivor #metoo #timesup #rapeculture #consentculture #survivor #makeyourvoiceheard #writer #humanrights #activist #humanist #lifestlye #influencer #entrepreneur

text:
the following is a true story of a survivor of human trafficking. this story includes sensitive language surrounding sexual assault. please consider this before reading further:⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
"ella* is an american girl who had been in the foster care system for years. it was family after family. home after home. her life was always changing. when she turned 18, she was too old to stay in the system. she felt hurt and alone with nowhere to go and no one to turn to. one day, a woman approached her asking if she needed any food or help. ella thought this woman really cared about her. the woman said her boyfriend was a good guy and could take care of her, and ella chose to trust her.⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
while everything seemed okay at first, the boyfriend suddenly told ella that she owed him money for everything he had provided for her. he began trafficking her, forcing her to go from city to city...⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
but one day, ella met with a man who she thought was paying for a service. he turned out to be a law enforcement officer who offered to help. despite the risk, she trusted him and told him her story. the officer assisted her to safety, her trafficker was arrested, and she was connected with a21. the team at a21 was able to find her safe housing and provide the services she needed to start building the life she envisioned for herself."⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
we partner with a21 year after year to provide the funds to continue helping women like ella, in america and at their offices around the world. find out more at a21.org, and join us this dressember as we create more opportunities for girls like ella. ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
- photo and info credit from dressember.org⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
